et and ensure plenty of fluids. Avoid raw or undercooked foods during chemo.", "created_at": "2026-03-01T02:06:11.778Z"}}, {"model": "planner.aichat", "pk": 5, "fields": {"user": ["Rabin"], "patient": 4, "query": "i am suffering from vomiting", "response": "I'm your Onco Assistant. Ginger tea or dry crackers can help. Ensure they stay hydrated. If vomiting is frequent, use the prescribed anti-nausea meds and inform the doctor.", "created_at": "2026-03-01T02:09:01.323Z"}}, {"model": "planner.aichat", "pk": 6, "fields": {"user": ["Rabin"], "patient": 4, "query": "fever", "response": "I'm your Onco Assistant. Fever is critical. If temperature is over 100.4°F (38°C), contact your oncology team immediately. Do not give fever-reducing meds without their permission.", "created_at": "2026-03-01T02:09:14.468Z"}}, {"model": "planner.aichat", "pk": 7, "fields": {"user": ["Rabin"], "patient": 4, "query": "vomiting", "response": "I'm your Onco Assistant. Ginger tea or dry crackers can help. Ensure they stay hydrated. If vomiting is frequent, use the prescribed anti-nausea meds and inform the doctor.", "created_at": "2026-03-01T04:34:44.214Z"}}, {"model": "planner.aichat", "pk": 8, "fields": {"user": ["Rabin"], "patient": 4, "query": "I am vomiting", "response": "I'm your Onco Assistant. Ginger tea or dry crackers can help. Ensure they stay hydrated. If vomiting is frequent, use the prescribed anti-nausea meds and inform the doctor.", "created_at": "2026-03-01T05:01:49.333Z"}}, {"model": "planner.aichat", "pk": 9, "fields": {"user": ["Rabin"], "patient": 4, "query": "i am feeling weakness and what medicine should i take", "response": "I'm your Onco Assistant. Fatigue is common during treatment. Encourage rest periods between activities. Short walks can actually help improve energy levels.", "created_at": "2026-03-01T05:02:14.072Z"}}, {"model": "planner.bloodreport", "pk": 1, "fields": {"patient": 3, "report_file": "reports/IMG_1931.jpeg", "cbc_count": "Pending", "pbs_count": "", 